{
  "texts": [
    "The proof that V is a B-continuous viscosity supersolution is analogous.",
    "For φ ∈ C 1,2 ((0, T) × E) and h ∈ C 1,2 ((0, T) × R), let ψ = φ + h(t, ∥X∥) be a test function as in Definition A.2, and let V -ψ have a strict, global maximum at (t, X) ∈ (0, T) × E.",
    "We need to show that",
    "Tr(Σ(X)(Σ(X)) * D 2 ψ(t, X))+⟨⟨X, A * Dφ(t, X)⟩⟩+ H(X, Dψ(t, X)) ≥ 0.",
    "Recall that A n i = (i-1 n, i n), i = 1,."
  ]
}